body:
@AlohaWebSolutions I described what needs to be done. I also said, that copying config won't help in most cases. If you are willing to take another approach, you can try the following. Assuming you are using default Ubuntu, your keyring will be the gnome one. So install the tool "seahorse". That tool allows you to browse the active keyrings. For my local setup it looks like this:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2179736/157286998-5a9f4c62-f42c-45e5-ad71-64a5215c1539.png)

The interesting part is the part before the hyphen. I suspect you'll find entries where the version number is part of the description.

@tmysik Thank you for your review!
@oyarzun  Thank you for your verification!
Merging.
